{"id":"balah","term":"Balah","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>A city in the tribe of Simeon (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Joshua 19:3\">Josh. 19:3</a>), elsewhere called Bilhah (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 4:29\">1 Chr. 4:29</a>) and Baalah (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Joshua 15:29\">Josh. 15:29</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Joshua 19:3","1 Chronicles 4:29","Joshua 15:29"]}